  <title>Description</title>
  <titlealts>
    <searchtitle>NHS Business Definition: Nurse (Level One) - Description</searchtitle>
  </titlealts>
  <body>

  <p>
A 
    <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
            keyref="business_definition_nurse__level_one_">Nurse (Level One)</xref>
 is a 
    <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_care_professional">CARE PROFESSIONAL</xref>
.  </p>
  <p>
      <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_nurse">NURSES</xref>
 trained within the United Kingdom may initially join the 
    <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
            keyref="business_definition_nursing_and_midwifery_council_register">Nursing and Midwifery Council Register</xref>
 as a 
    <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
            keyref="business_definition_nurse__level_one_">Level One Nurse</xref>
, also known as a 
    <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
            keyref="business_definition_nurse__level_one_">Registered Nurse</xref>
, after the 
    <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
            keyref="business_definition_nursing_and_midwifery_council">Nursing and Midwifery Council</xref>
 receives course completion details and declaration of good character from the Higher Education Institution where they qualified.  </p>
  <p>
This reflects a standard of proficiency considered necessary for safe and effective practice under Level 1 Nurses Sub-part 1 of the 
    <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
            keyref="business_definition_nursing_and_midwifery_council_register">Nursing and Midwifery Council Register</xref>
.  </p>
  <p>
      <i>
Note: 
      <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_nurse">NURSES</xref>
 trained within the European Union or Overseas can also join the 
      <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
               keyref="business_definition_nursing_and_midwifery_council_register">Nursing and Midwifery Council Register</xref>
 as a 
      <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
               keyref="business_definition_nurse__level_one_">Level One Nurse</xref>
. See the 
      <xref href="https://www.nmc.org.uk/" scope="external" format="html">Nursing and Midwifery Council website</xref>
 for the requirements.    </i>
  </p>
  <p>
Registration as a 
    <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
            keyref="business_definition_nurse__level_one_">Level One Nurse</xref>
 (
    <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
            keyref="business_definition_nurse__level_one_">Registered Nurse</xref>
) will be in one of four fields of practice:  </p>
  <ol>
      <li>
         <div>
            <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
                  keyref="business_definition_adult_nursing">Adult Nursing</xref>
         </div>
      </li>
      <li>
         <div>
            <xref href="http://www.datadictionary.nhs.uk/web_site_content/supporting_definitions/mental_health_nursing.asp"
                  scope="external"
                  format="html">Mental_Health_Nursing</xref>
         </div>
      </li>
      <li>
         <div>
            <xref href="http://www.datadictionary.nhs.uk/web_site_content/supporting_definitions/learning_disabilities_nursing.asp"
                  scope="external"
                  format="html">Learning_Disabilities_Nursing</xref>
         </div>
      </li>
      <li>
         <div>
            <xref href="http://www.datadictionary.nhs.uk/web_site_content/supporting_definitions/children's_nursing.asp"
                  scope="external"
                  format="html">Children's_Nursing</xref>
            <p>.</p>
         </div>
      </li>
  </ol>

